annot.p: S solo and coro (6), A solo and coro (6), T solo and coro (6), B solo and coro (4), org (5)

This source has been extensively modified to allow a performance without violins: (1) In the Gloria, bars 8–38 and 73–93 have been removed, while bars 39–72 comprise the lyrics “Laudamus te” to “Amen”. (2) The Credo, Benedictus (including its Osanna), and Agnus Dei (only bars 1–13) have been replaced with movements by an unidentified author. (3) The Amen fugue of the original Credo has been reworked to the Osanna in the Sanctus.
